Text.Value: Wasn't... a sheep...
Leave.
Why are you so worried about your sister?
*The spell's power wanes. You can ask no more questions.*
Do you have any family?
Did you find your sister?
Where are you from?
Demir...
Why did you accuse Ethel of taking Mayrina?
Farm... out by... Baldur's Gate.
... gotta get Mayrina back... for Mam...
*The corpse does not stir. It will answer no more questions.*
What killed you?
Connor was... her husband. Childhood... sweethearts. He died... and she nearly... broke.
My sister... went to Ethel...
Because what... Mayrina wants... only hag... can give.
I found this letter. Who is Connor?
Heard her... screaming. But not... real.
Mam... Johl... Mayrina... and soon... a niece.
Hags... play with... their food.
Don't drink... the water...
*Eyes filled with fear, the corpse will not speak with you.*
Why are you so worried about your sister?
Who are you?
Husband died... wants him... wants him back.
*The corpse regards you lifelessly.*
Why did you accuse Ethel of taking Mayrina?
This place seems strange. Anything I should be wary of?
We're in the middle of nowhere. Why come here?

Synopsis: Demir, the eldest brother, has died. The following dialogue is a call to action for the player and directs them towards Mayrina and the hag.
